"LALOCA is the Laboratory for Locative Media and GPS Films. It's a centre for the production and research of mobile media at the Federal University of Juiz de Fora in collaboration with the University of California San Diego. The projects focus on locative cinema with interactive scripts based on open source OS and tools, as HiperGps, HiperGeo and walkingtools, whose project The Transborder Immigrant Tool has caused great media frenzy and issues with the government for Ricardo Dominguez, professor, activist and one of the developers of the tool."
(http://www.furtherfield.org/features/reviews/celebrating-brazilian-open-digital-culture-festival-cultura-digital)


